    {
        "content": "<p>With <code>norm_num</code> I get the in goal <code>0.5 = 2⁻¹</code></p>",
        "id": 569137760,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1768947486
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It works for me:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">0.5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 569138041,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1768947622
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>by hint</code> says that <code>by bound</code> works as well. you could try that instead.</p>",
        "id": 569138142,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1768947667
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, okay, I was not importing the hole of Mathlib, that's why it didn't work for me</p>",
        "id": 569138694,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1768947940
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you know what should I import if I want to use it with out having to import the whole Mathlib?</p>",
        "id": 569138777,
        "sender_full_name": "Iván Renison",
        "timestamp": 1768947974
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>#min_imports</code> will tell you:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">0.5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">min_imports</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- import Mathlib.Analysis.RCLike.Basic</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 569139353,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1768948221
    },
